Actionable feedback structured by the requested aspects

1) Correctness
- Relation choice: Many assertions describe one quantity being reduced by another (e.g., "shortening of fallow period" produces a reduction of herbaceous cover). For such direct monotonic effects prefer the canonical relation DECREASES rather than CAUSES. Use CAUSES when the sentence supports a generic causal claim that is not explicitly phrased as an increase/decrease of a measurable quantity.
