- Avoid losing a relation because one side is expressed as a change phrase; normalize so you can link the base concepts.

3) Clarity
- Argument spans: Use concise noun phrases (canonical forms) for arguments:
  - "shortening of fallow period" → acceptable, but prefer consistent form (e.g., "shortened fallow period" or "shortening of the fallow period") across examples.
