  5) Strip hedges/parentheticals and duplicate canonical spans.
- Clarify agent vs. patient direction for causal/change relations: prefer the pattern (agent/driver, INCREASES/DECREASES, landcover cover) only when text explicitly frames the actor as causing a quantitative change. Otherwise, frame the preservation/protection as an event and link timing/location to that event.
- Make deduplication deterministic: enforce canonical label mapping across triples so the same phenomenon uses identical labels (e.g., always "NTFP-providing trees" and "protection of NTFP-providing trees").

Compact actionable checklist to incorporate into the system prompt
- Add explicit trigger lists for each predicate (whitelist/blacklist) and use them for predicate choice.
- Make eventization rules mandatory for OCCURS_DURING and when percent/time qualifiers appear.
- Disallow CAUSES unless a causal trigger from whitelist is present; treat protect/preserve as agentive (eventize) unless comparative/change words exist.
- Require final validation checklist above before emitting any triple.
- Enforce canonical pluralization/event-naming rules and deterministic deduplication.

These changes keep the fixed predicate set intact but make the extraction behavior far more conservative and consistent, reducing false causal claims, standardizing event/subject forms, and improving coverage of supported temporal/agent/location relations.
