  - Treat "of" as locative only when the head noun is a locatable place/landcover (forest, field, village); otherwise treat "of" as ownership/qualification and do NOT emit LOCATED_IN unless additional locative wording is present.
  - Treat possessive markers ('s, of X) with the same locative heuristics above.
- Subject direction rule: require the subject of LOCATED_IN to be the entity that is located (not the container). If sentence is ambiguous, prefer the token that is syntactically the NP being placed (object of preposition in/in/on).
- CAUSES strictness (reinforce current rule): require one of the exact CAUSES whitelist cues as a dependency head connecting the two clauses (e.g., "caused", "led to", "resulted in", "because"). Add: if the causal cue is subordinating (“because”) verify it links the clauses semantically (not a parenthetical).
- Blacklist enforcement: explicitly forbid mapping protect/preserve/manage/help/use/support → CAUSES; add a check that prevents CAUSES even when passive agent structures are present without whitelist cues.

2) Completeness — ensure informative arguments, nested locations, and eventization are captured
